experiments_run.name: Constructive v1 (alternating + interlocking)
experiments_run.notes: Tried multiple angle combinations (0/180, 45/225, 90/270, etc.) and spacing optimization. All configurations worse than baseline.

experiments_run.name: Improved zaburo pattern
experiments_run.notes: Optimized row configuration and spacing. Best config for N=10: n_even=3, n_odd=2, h=0.7, v=1.0. Still 28% worse than baseline.

analysis.gap: Constructive approaches achieve ~88 vs baseline 70.6 (25% worse)
analysis.reason: Baseline uses sophisticated interlocking patterns that simple grid-based approaches cannot replicate. The baseline is the result of C++ SA with millions of iterations.

conclusion: Constructive approaches cannot match the baseline. The baseline uses sophisticated interlocking patterns optimized by C++ SA. Without access to similar optimization power, we cannot improve on the baseline. Submitted baseline as-is.
